<item>
            <title>[HIVE-1846] change hive assumption that local mode mappers/reducers always run in same jvm </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-1846</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;we are trying out a version of hadoop local mode that runs multiple mappers/reducers by spawning jvm&apos;s for them. In this mode hive mappers fail in reading the plan file. it seems that we assume (in the setMapredWork call) that local mode mappers/reducers will run in the same jvm (we can cache the current plan in a global var and don&apos;t serialize to a path). this needs to get fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
